cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper analyzes the performance of LRU caches under the Shot Noise Model, which is proposed to better capture the characteristics of Video on Demand (VoD) traffic. This makes it highly relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture sub-category.
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper investigates the validity of Che's approximation for LRU caches, which involves analyzing the eviction time of cache items. This is a classic problem in the Data Structures and Algorithms sub-category.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper derives upper and lower bounds for the hit probability in tandem networks of caches under Che's approximation. This involves analyzing the information content of the cache requests and is therefore relevant to the Information Theory sub-category.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of LRU caches under a specific traffic model, which can be seen as a system with inputs (cache requests) and outputs (cache hits/misses). This makes it relevant to the Systems and Control sub-category.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper focuses on the Shot Noise Model, which is proposed to better capture the characteristics of Video on Demand (VoD) traffic. This makes it relevant to the Multimedia sub-category.
